122 OCTAVIUS

Diagoras, surnamed the Atheist, was a disciple of Democritus of Abdera and had some fame as a lyric poet. He fied from Athens (411 Rc.) to avoid trial on a charge of impiety. Of. Tat. Ad Graec. 27 ; Plut. Plac. Phil. 1. 7.
